WEBVTT

00:02.502 --> 00:04.137
[***]

00:04.170 --> 00:05.705
NARRATOR:
<i>In Bed-Stuy, a lot of people</i>

00:05.739 --> 00:09.342
<i>have reputations</i>
<i>for different things.</i>

00:09.376 --> 00:12.278
<i>Diedre Garfield was 23</i>
<i>and had a reputation</i>

00:12.312 --> 00:14.647
<i>for being the youngest</i>
<i>grandmother in Brooklyn.</i>

00:14.681 --> 00:16.282
[WHISTLE BLOWING]

00:16.316 --> 00:18.318
All right, I got everything
under control!

00:18.351 --> 00:21.421
NARRATOR:
<i>Mr. Jackson had a reputation</i>
<i>for being crazy as hell.</i>

00:21.454 --> 00:23.857
<i>And a lot of people say</i>
<i>he invented homelessness.</i>

00:23.890 --> 00:26.393
Move the car!
You want to fight?

00:26.426 --> 00:28.695
NARRATOR:
<i>I had a reputation too.</i>

00:28.728 --> 00:32.465
<i>Not only for being a nerd</i>
<i>or getting beat up every day,</i>

00:32.499 --> 00:34.367
<i>I was also known for being</i>

00:34.401 --> 00:37.103
<i>the best Asteroids player</i>
<i>in Bed-Stuy.</i>

00:37.137 --> 00:39.239
[***]

00:46.212 --> 00:47.480
[CHANGE JINGLING]

00:50.417 --> 00:53.153
<i>I'd beat people from all over:</i>

00:53.186 --> 00:54.788
<i>Chinatown...</i>

00:54.821 --> 00:56.556
<i>Rikers...</i>

00:56.589 --> 00:57.857
<i>the Village...</i>

00:57.891 --> 00:59.359
<i>Even though I was a nerd,</i>

00:59.392 --> 01:01.194
<i>it felt really good</i>

01:01.227 --> 01:04.397
<i>that there was one thing</i>
<i>that nobody could beat me at.</i>

01:04.431 --> 01:07.233
Chris, somebody beat your score
last night.

01:07.267 --> 01:10.236
NARRATOR:
<i>Hey, even Mike Tyson</i>
<i>got knocked out.</i>

01:10.270 --> 01:12.172
[***]

01:14.207 --> 01:15.608
NARRATOR:
<i>Ain't this about a--</i>

01:15.642 --> 01:17.610
[***]

01:23.583 --> 01:26.619
<i>* Aw, make it funky now </i>

01:53.646 --> 01:56.649
NARRATOR:
<i>My mother had paying bills</i>
<i>down to a science,</i>

01:56.683 --> 01:59.886
<i>but there were always things</i>
<i>she didn't count on.</i>

01:59.919 --> 02:02.622
Oh, damn it!

02:02.655 --> 02:04.557
Hey, honey.

02:04.591 --> 02:06.726
Hey, baby.
What's wrong?

02:06.760 --> 02:08.561
Well, I used this
month's phone bill

02:08.595 --> 02:10.563
to pay half of last month's
electric bill,

02:10.597 --> 02:12.699
and now I don't have
enough for the gas bill.

02:12.732 --> 02:15.435
Well, why don't you just use
the electric bill money

02:15.468 --> 02:16.636
to pay the electric bill?

02:16.670 --> 02:18.438
Well, Tonya had to
get a filling.

02:18.471 --> 02:20.840
She had a cavity.
She did?

02:20.874 --> 02:23.877
NARRATOR:
<i>My father never knew when</i>
<i>there was anything wrong</i>

02:23.910 --> 02:27.213
<i>with the kids unless we were</i>
<i>unconscious or in the hospital.</i>

02:27.247 --> 02:29.916
Oh... Oh, no, no, no.

02:29.949 --> 02:31.651
We're gonna have to cut back.

02:31.685 --> 02:32.986
Cut back on what?

02:33.019 --> 02:36.256
I mean, we're barely
getting by as it is.

02:36.289 --> 02:39.526
NARRATOR:
<i>That look only meant one thing.</i>

02:39.559 --> 02:42.462
Oh, no. Uh-uh.
Uh-uh, not my turtles.

02:42.495 --> 02:43.997
You are not taking
away my turtles.

02:44.030 --> 02:46.399
NARRATOR:
<i>My mother loved</i>
<i>chocolate turtles</i>

02:46.433 --> 02:48.268
<i>more than anything else</i>
<i>in the world.</i>

02:48.301 --> 02:49.803
<i>Whenever she ate one,</i>

02:49.836 --> 02:52.539
<i>it was like all of life's</i>
<i>problems just went away.</i>

02:52.572 --> 02:55.675
[TV BLARING]
[ALL SHOUTING]

03:04.284 --> 03:06.319
[***]

03:10.824 --> 03:13.426
NARRATOR:
<i>It's a good thing</i>
<i>she chose those turtles</i>

03:13.460 --> 03:14.861
<i>instead of guns.</i>

03:14.894 --> 03:17.564
Those chocolate turtles
are costing us $12 a box.

03:17.597 --> 03:20.667
Oh. You gotta take
away my turtles.

03:20.700 --> 03:23.837
You know
I need my turtles.

03:23.870 --> 03:26.306
Why don't you cut off
your lottery playing?

03:26.339 --> 03:27.974
Pssh. I'm not cutting
out my numbers.

03:28.008 --> 03:29.442
Oh!

03:29.476 --> 03:31.745
If you don't play,
how can you expect to win?

03:31.778 --> 03:33.680
Look, it says so right here.

03:33.713 --> 03:34.681
Oh, no, no, no.

03:34.714 --> 03:36.816
No that damn
dream book.

03:36.850 --> 03:38.752
NARRATOR:
<i>My dad was the most</i>
<i>level-headed person I knew,</i>

03:38.785 --> 03:40.854
<i>except when it came</i>
<i>to playing the lottery,</i>

03:40.887 --> 03:43.857
<i>and he always consulted</i>
<i>his lucky star dream book.</i>

03:43.890 --> 03:46.793
<i>A dream book takes any</i>
<i>possible dream you can have</i>

03:46.826 --> 03:48.828
<i>and transforms it</i>
<i>into a lucky number.</i>

03:48.862 --> 03:50.897
You dreamt about a monkey
on the train

03:50.930 --> 03:52.365
in the middle of a blizzard.

03:52.399 --> 03:54.634
Here it is: 8-1-4.

03:54.668 --> 03:56.603
I dreamt Dr. J
was roller-skating

03:56.636 --> 03:59.305
with two white women
in Sweden.

03:59.339 --> 04:02.742
Here it is: 6-2-1.

04:02.776 --> 04:04.477
White ladies?

04:04.511 --> 04:06.346
Rochelle, if I win
the lottery,

04:06.379 --> 04:08.548
you can buy all the
chocolate turtles you want.

04:08.581 --> 04:11.351
But you eating chocolate turtles
ain't helping nobody.

04:11.384 --> 04:12.986
Well, if you
play the lottery,

04:13.019 --> 04:15.622
I'm eating my turtles.

04:15.655 --> 04:19.626
Fine...I'll quit the lottery.

04:19.659 --> 04:21.361
Okay, then.

04:21.394 --> 04:24.064
NARRATOR:
<i>Can you believe</i>
<i>this is a real argument?</i>

04:24.097 --> 04:25.765
[STUDENTS CLAPPING]

04:25.799 --> 04:28.501
<i>At school, even Greg</i>
<i>was getting a reputation.</i>

04:28.535 --> 04:32.505
And for Best Attendance...
Greg Wuliger!

04:32.539 --> 04:34.641
Yes!
[STUDENTS CLAPPING]

04:37.644 --> 04:39.646
NARRATOR:
<i>Getting an award for attendance</i>

04:39.679 --> 04:42.048
<i>is kind of like getting</i>
<i>an award for breathing.</i>

04:42.082 --> 04:44.517
[***]

04:44.551 --> 04:47.954
Wait, your dad is giving you
$5 just for coming to school?

04:47.987 --> 04:50.924
I bet him I wouldn't miss a day
this year. So far, so good.

04:50.957 --> 04:53.960
NARRATOR:
<i>My mother told me I'd better</i>
<i>not miss a day of school</i>

04:53.993 --> 04:55.795
<i>or else she'd take $5</i>
<i>off my ass.</i>

04:55.829 --> 04:57.831
This is so cool.
NARRATOR:<i>The only award</i>

04:57.864 --> 05:00.367
<i>I could've gotten at Corleone</i>
<i>would've been...</i>

05:00.400 --> 05:04.537
For Taking the Best
Ass Whupping... Chris.

05:04.571 --> 05:06.539
[STUDENTS CLAPPING]

05:06.573 --> 05:08.541
Yes! Yes! Yes, yes, yes!

05:08.575 --> 05:10.710
[***]

05:23.923 --> 05:26.960
NARRATOR:
<i>But instead of an award,</i>
<i>I had Asteroids.</i>

05:26.993 --> 05:30.563
Hey, I got the top five scores
on Asteroids yesterday.

05:30.597 --> 05:32.399
Get out of here.
No way.

05:32.432 --> 05:35.402
Yeah, but some kid
beat me.

05:35.435 --> 05:36.870
I have to protect my title.

05:36.903 --> 05:40.073
Man, you're just like
Apollo Creed in<i>Rocky II.</i>

05:40.106 --> 05:41.841
You sure you can
beat this guy?

05:41.875 --> 05:45.612
Hey, I've got a reputation
to maintain.

05:46.746 --> 05:48.682
Hey, Tonya, ask Daddy
for some money

05:48.715 --> 05:50.483
so we can get
some candy tomorrow.

05:50.517 --> 05:51.785
How come you can't ask?

05:51.818 --> 05:55.155
Because if I ask,
he'll give me a speech.

05:55.188 --> 05:57.123
If you ask, he'll
give you the money.

05:57.157 --> 05:58.858
If Daddy gives me the money,

05:58.892 --> 06:01.161
you have to share
some of that candy with me.

06:01.194 --> 06:03.863
Okay.
All right.

06:03.897 --> 06:05.565
[***]

06:08.501 --> 06:10.170
JULIUS:
Six...

06:14.207 --> 06:15.475
Daddy.

06:15.508 --> 06:16.543
Huh? What?

06:16.576 --> 06:17.811
Can I have a dollar?

06:17.844 --> 06:19.713
What do you need a dollar for?

06:19.746 --> 06:22.615
I want to get Drew some, um...
some candy.

06:22.649 --> 06:25.752
Oh...that's nice.

06:25.785 --> 06:28.021
NARRATOR:
<i>My father was crazy</i>
<i>about Tonya.</i>

06:28.054 --> 06:30.490
<i>She was the only one</i>
<i>in the house who would dare</i>

06:30.523 --> 06:33.059
<i>take sleep and money from him</i>
<i>at the same time.</i>

06:33.093 --> 06:35.161
Thanks, Daddy.

06:35.195 --> 06:38.565
NARRATOR:
<i>In Bed-Stuy, we never had</i>
<i>a real video arcade to go to.</i>

06:38.598 --> 06:39.966
<i>All we had was Doc's.</i>

06:40.000 --> 06:42.469
<i>At Doc's, you can get</i>
<i>almost anything.</i>

06:42.502 --> 06:43.937
<i>You could cash a check.</i>

06:43.970 --> 06:46.006
That'll be $5.

06:46.039 --> 06:47.774
NARRATOR:
<i>You could get an alibi.</i>

06:47.807 --> 06:50.844
Nah, it wasn't him.
He was here.

06:52.245 --> 06:54.047
That'll be $5.

06:54.080 --> 06:56.916
NARRATOR:
<i>You could even get</i>
<i>your teeth pulled.</i>

06:56.950 --> 06:58.051
Ah...
Open.

06:58.084 --> 06:59.886
Ah!

06:59.919 --> 07:01.921
[SCREAMS]

07:03.957 --> 07:06.226
Your mama know you're down here?
Yes, sir.

07:06.259 --> 07:09.029
NARRATOR:
<i>My mother didn't like me</i>
<i>hanging out at Doc's</i>

07:09.062 --> 07:12.065
<i>'cause she thought that would</i>
<i>eventually lead to this...</i>

07:12.098 --> 07:13.566
I'm a junkie.

07:13.600 --> 07:15.602
A crackhead.

07:15.635 --> 07:18.705
Look, just tell my ma
her oldest son is a crackhead.

07:18.738 --> 07:20.707
Hey! Little dude
from across the street.

07:20.740 --> 07:22.642
NARRATOR:
<i>Usually Jerome would rob me,</i>

07:22.676 --> 07:24.744
<i>but not when I was about</i>
<i>to play Asteroids.</i>

07:24.778 --> 07:26.579
You getting ready
to play Asteroids?

07:26.613 --> 07:27.847
Yeah. Some kid
beat my score.

07:27.881 --> 07:30.083
For real? Oh, no!
I know you're not

07:30.116 --> 07:31.685
gonna take that, man.

07:31.718 --> 07:33.186
You'd better protect your rep.

07:33.219 --> 07:35.755
[GAME CHIMING]

07:35.789 --> 07:37.857
NARRATOR:
<i>If I didn't get</i>
<i>my high score back,</i>

07:37.891 --> 07:39.859
<i>somebody was gonna</i>
<i>get hit with a brick.</i>

07:39.893 --> 07:42.228
<i>* I'm the boy wonder</i>
<i>Tragic super duper *</i>

07:42.262 --> 07:43.897
<i>* Raised in the Bridge </i>

07:43.930 --> 07:45.699
<i>* 'Cause I'm</i>
<i>A Queensbridge trooper *</i>

07:45.732 --> 07:47.233
Come on, come on.
Do it. Do it.

07:47.267 --> 07:49.869
<i>* '88 is on the way</i>
<i>I make a big difference *</i>

07:49.903 --> 07:52.906
<i>* I make it visual</i>
<i>And intellectually clear *</i>

07:52.939 --> 07:55.642
<i>* The rebel is here </i>

07:59.112 --> 08:01.047
BOY:
You're Chris.

08:02.215 --> 08:04.017
NARRATOR:
<i>Hey, he's big.</i>

08:04.050 --> 08:05.251
So you're Doah.

08:05.285 --> 08:07.620
What?

08:08.221 --> 08:09.756
Doah.

08:11.157 --> 08:12.726
That's DOA.

08:12.759 --> 08:14.694
It means dead on arrival.

08:14.728 --> 08:17.130
My name is Jorge.

08:17.163 --> 08:18.998
So what,
you want to play?

08:19.032 --> 08:20.734
Come on.

08:20.767 --> 08:22.635
NARRATOR:
<i>I know it looks strange,</i>
<i>but before people</i>

08:22.669 --> 08:24.170
<i>got Play Stations</i>
<i>in their backseats,</i>

08:24.204 --> 08:27.107
<i>you actually had to go</i>
<i>someplace to play video games.</i>

08:27.140 --> 08:30.176
[***]

08:30.210 --> 08:31.644
Come on.

08:31.678 --> 08:33.213
<i>* ...man on a mission </i>

08:33.246 --> 08:35.815
<i>* Diagnosing the story</i>
<i>Like a mental condition *</i>

08:35.849 --> 08:37.984
<i>* Everybody wants</i>
<i>A piece of the pie *</i>

08:38.018 --> 08:40.153
<i>* Living the life</i>
<i>Or is it living a lie? *</i>

08:40.186 --> 08:42.856
<i>* Got your eyes</i>
<i>On the prize *</i>

08:42.889 --> 08:45.959
[ALL CHEERING, CHATTERING]

08:45.992 --> 08:49.329
All right, man,
that was a good game.

08:50.330 --> 08:52.098
Hey, hold up.
Where are you going?

08:52.132 --> 08:53.600
I gotta get home.

08:53.633 --> 08:55.235
What, you're not gonna
give him a rematch?

08:55.268 --> 08:58.071
Yeah, you can't just beat
the man and walk out.

08:58.104 --> 09:00.040
Hey, I really gotta go.

09:00.073 --> 09:02.075
Besides,
I'll just beat him again.

09:02.108 --> 09:03.843
Ooh...

09:03.877 --> 09:07.047
Want to put some money
on that?

09:07.080 --> 09:09.249
NARRATOR:
<i>If you have a good reputation,</i>

09:09.282 --> 09:12.152
<i>you have to be willing</i>
<i>to do anything to protect it.</i>

09:12.185 --> 09:13.820
I can't play for money.

09:13.853 --> 09:15.321
CROWD:
Aw...

09:15.355 --> 09:18.158
Don't tell me you're scared.
I'm not.

09:18.191 --> 09:19.726
I just gotta go home.

09:19.759 --> 09:23.663
Man, I can't believe
you're scared of this dude.

09:23.697 --> 09:25.965
Come on, go, get, come on.

09:25.999 --> 09:27.767
NARRATOR:
<i>Anybody got five bucks?</i>

09:27.801 --> 09:32.105
<i>* Everybody hates Chris </i>

09:38.044 --> 09:39.846
CHRIS:
Hey, I need a favor.

09:39.879 --> 09:42.048
I need to borrow
your five dollars.

09:42.082 --> 09:44.084
What? What do
you need it for?

09:44.117 --> 09:45.952
I beat this kid
playing Asteroids,

09:45.985 --> 09:47.921
and now he wants
to play for money.

09:47.954 --> 09:50.123
Can't you just save up
your lunch money?

09:50.156 --> 09:52.025
Or take your neighbor's
garbage out?

09:52.058 --> 09:54.728
Or help small ladies carry
groceries to their car?

09:54.761 --> 09:56.429
Or turn in some Coke bottles
or something?

09:56.463 --> 09:59.799
NARRATOR:
<i>Note to self:</i>
<i>when begging, be persistent.</i>

09:59.833 --> 10:02.335
Hey, I don't have time
for this.

10:02.369 --> 10:05.338
You got to do this, or my
reputation's gonna be ruined.

10:05.372 --> 10:10.210
NARRATOR:
<i>I wonder if that's how O.J.</i>
<i>got A.C. to drive that Bronco.</i>

10:10.243 --> 10:12.779
[EXHALES]
Thanks.

10:12.812 --> 10:14.681
[***]

10:15.849 --> 10:17.450
NARRATOR:
<i>After a day with no turtles,</i>

10:17.484 --> 10:21.955
<i>my mother was going through</i>
<i>serious sugar withdrawal.</i>

10:21.988 --> 10:24.691
Ooh! Ooh!

10:24.724 --> 10:28.061
NARRATOR:
<i>She'd eat any sugar</i>
<i>she could find.</i>

10:30.764 --> 10:32.365
<i>From anywhere</i>
<i>she could find it.</i>

10:32.399 --> 10:34.868
[GRUNTS, THEN LAUGHS]

10:34.901 --> 10:37.103
NARRATOR:
<i>All I can tell you is that</i>

10:37.137 --> 10:40.740
<i>crack ain't got nothin'</i>
<i>on chocolate turtles.</i>

10:42.976 --> 10:44.144
Here.

10:44.177 --> 10:46.046
NARRATOR:
<i>Drew was getting his fix too.</i>

10:46.079 --> 10:48.014
I know you're giving me
more than that.

10:48.048 --> 10:50.383
You're not supposed to be
eating candy, anyway.

10:50.417 --> 10:52.318
You just got a filling.

10:52.352 --> 10:54.220
I'm telling Mama!

10:54.254 --> 10:56.222
[***]

11:03.196 --> 11:07.767
NARRATOR:
<i>Some people had wine,</i>
<i>my mom had Aunt Jemima.</i>

11:15.775 --> 11:17.310
Oh, see...
Mama!

11:17.344 --> 11:20.914
Drew got some candy, and this is
all he gave me, three p-- Ma!

11:20.947 --> 11:22.248
Candy?
Did you say candy?

11:22.282 --> 11:23.283
Yeah?

11:23.316 --> 11:24.751
Drew, get in here!

11:26.920 --> 11:28.822
You got candy?
Ma!

11:28.855 --> 11:31.157
Don't "Ma" me.
Don't "Ma" me right now, boy.

11:31.191 --> 11:33.026
Do you have anything
in here that...

11:33.059 --> 11:35.762
[SNIFFING]
...that tastes like turtles?

11:35.795 --> 11:37.163
No.
Something that has

11:37.197 --> 11:39.232
chocolate, peanuts, caramel,
something like that?

11:39.265 --> 11:40.834
I don't know.

11:40.867 --> 11:42.302
Where in the world
did you get money for candy?

11:42.335 --> 11:44.404
Daddy.

11:44.437 --> 11:45.505
[***]

11:45.538 --> 11:47.874
CROWD:
Ooh!

11:49.476 --> 11:51.244
Now, that's what
I'm talking about.

11:51.277 --> 11:53.446
NARRATOR:
<i>What he's actually</i>
<i>talking about is</i>

11:53.480 --> 11:54.981
<i>which one of us he's gonna rob</i>

11:55.015 --> 11:57.183
<i>after we get through</i>
<i>with the game.</i>

11:58.985 --> 12:01.254
Ha!
Oh, whoa!
Wh-Wh-What's wrong with you!

12:01.287 --> 12:03.923
Turtles!

12:03.957 --> 12:07.961
I ain't got my turtles!

12:07.994 --> 12:10.030
I'm over here drinking syrup

12:10.063 --> 12:13.833
while you're still
buying lottery tickets.

12:13.867 --> 12:16.569
What's wrong with me?

12:16.603 --> 12:18.805
What's wrong with you?

12:18.838 --> 12:20.940
Baby, I did it for you.

12:20.974 --> 12:24.077
Julius, we both had
an agreement.

12:24.110 --> 12:27.447
And you have to honor
that agreement.

12:27.480 --> 12:31.484
Do you know what kind of message
we are sending to our children?

12:31.518 --> 12:34.020
Message?
You're telling our kids,

12:34.054 --> 12:37.223
"Oh, go ahead, little children,
ignore your mother,

12:37.257 --> 12:38.291
'cause she's a lunatic!"

12:38.324 --> 12:40.226
I didn't say that!
Yes, you did!

12:40.260 --> 12:43.229
What I meant was,
it's just... It's...

12:43.263 --> 12:45.031
It's just a couple
of dollars.

12:45.065 --> 12:48.335
Are we cutting back?

12:48.368 --> 12:53.039
Or am I...cutting back?

12:53.073 --> 12:55.075
[CRYING]
'Cause I can't do it
by myself.

12:55.108 --> 12:58.111
Ah, baby, no, baby.
I feel alone.

12:58.144 --> 13:00.947
No, no, we-we're cutting back,
we're cutting back, okay?

13:00.980 --> 13:03.216
I'm sorry.
We can do this!

13:03.249 --> 13:04.918
We can do this.

13:04.951 --> 13:08.221
I get the shakes at night,
Julius, I get the shakes!

13:08.254 --> 13:11.157
It's all right,
we can do this.

13:11.191 --> 13:12.926
Okay.

13:14.361 --> 13:15.995
Okay.

13:16.029 --> 13:17.864
[***]

13:17.897 --> 13:19.332
Fine.

13:25.405 --> 13:27.140
[GROANS]
[WHOOPS]

13:27.173 --> 13:29.209
Yeah, baby!
Oh, yeah, baby!

13:29.242 --> 13:31.511
Watch out,
let me through.

13:31.544 --> 13:33.980
Good game.
You almost had him.

13:34.014 --> 13:35.982
You got a lot of heart,
little dude.

13:36.016 --> 13:39.019
NARRATOR:
<i>I wonder if I could sell</i>
<i>my heart for five dollars.</i>

13:39.052 --> 13:41.154
You lost?
How can you lose?

13:41.187 --> 13:43.890
Hey, I'll pay you back.
I'll...carry some groceries

13:43.923 --> 13:45.892
or return some soda bottles
or something.

13:45.925 --> 13:47.327
That crap'll take forever!

13:47.360 --> 13:49.295
Well, why'd you
tell me to do it?

13:49.329 --> 13:52.032
Because I didn't want
to give you my money?

13:52.065 --> 13:53.667
I'm as surprised
as you are.

13:53.700 --> 13:56.670
No. I'd say you're about 5 bucks
less surprised than I am.

13:56.703 --> 13:59.973
NARRATOR:
<i>He's starting to sound</i>
<i>like my father.</i>

14:00.006 --> 14:02.108
[***]

14:04.077 --> 14:07.080
Hey. I'm gonna
pay you back.

14:07.113 --> 14:09.449
It'll take a couple of weeks,
but I will.

14:09.482 --> 14:10.984
You got to play him again.

14:11.017 --> 14:13.486
No. I don't think so.

14:13.520 --> 14:15.321
What about your rep?

14:15.355 --> 14:17.323
I've got a new one:

14:17.357 --> 14:19.025
sucker.

14:20.293 --> 14:21.561
Come on.

14:25.065 --> 14:28.301
NARRATOR:
<i>I missed being the Asteroids</i>
<i>champ of Bed-Stuy.</i>

14:28.335 --> 14:30.403
<i>Without that,</i>
<i>I was just another bum</i>

14:30.437 --> 14:32.372
<i>from the neighborhood.</i>

14:41.247 --> 14:43.316
<i>My father wouldn't</i>
<i>usually admit</i>

14:43.350 --> 14:46.486
<i>he was wrong about things, at</i>
<i>least not in front of the kids.</i>

14:46.519 --> 14:48.488
I have something to say.

14:48.521 --> 14:50.724
NARRATOR:
<i>I thought he was about to</i>
<i>tell us he was leaving us</i>

14:50.757 --> 14:53.326
<i>for a white family</i>
<i>across town.</i>

14:53.360 --> 14:55.028
I'm sorry.

14:55.061 --> 14:56.329
What'd you do?

14:57.597 --> 15:00.133
After your mother gave up
her chocolate turtles

15:00.166 --> 15:03.103
so we could pay the bills...
I played the lottery.

15:03.136 --> 15:05.238
I shouldn't
have done that.

15:05.271 --> 15:07.173
I was wrong.

15:07.207 --> 15:09.142
Is that why she ate up
all our candy?

15:09.175 --> 15:12.145
I should've never given
you money for candy.

15:12.178 --> 15:15.648
Dad, um,
it's not all her fault.

15:15.682 --> 15:17.250
I asked her to do it.

15:17.283 --> 15:19.119
But only because I knew
you'd give it to her.

15:19.152 --> 15:20.453
How'd you know that?

15:20.487 --> 15:22.622
Because you give her
everything she wants.

15:22.655 --> 15:24.224
TONYA:
That's not true.

15:24.257 --> 15:26.693
One time I asked
if I could set Chris on fire,

15:26.726 --> 15:28.228
and he didn't
let me do that.

15:28.261 --> 15:31.164
Well, thank goodness
for that.

15:31.197 --> 15:33.533
I have a confession too.

15:33.566 --> 15:36.002
I've been hanging out
at that corner store.

15:36.036 --> 15:37.203
Chris...

15:37.237 --> 15:39.139
But I was only
playing Asteroids.

15:39.172 --> 15:41.541
Oh. Well, that ain't so bad.

15:41.574 --> 15:43.710
And I lost five dollars.

15:44.544 --> 15:46.146
What? Five dollars?

15:46.179 --> 15:47.647
Ooh! I'm telling!

15:47.681 --> 15:50.517
Now, who are you gonna tell?
We're all sitting right here.

15:50.550 --> 15:52.585
ROCHELLE:
How did you lose $5, boy?

15:52.619 --> 15:54.020
Where did you get $5?

15:54.054 --> 15:57.023
I bet a guy
playing Asteroids, and...

15:57.057 --> 15:59.159
and I got the $5 from Greg.

15:59.192 --> 16:01.194
What are you doing
betting on video games?

16:01.227 --> 16:03.296
CHRIS:
I was trying to protect
my reputation.

16:03.329 --> 16:04.798
DREW:
You have a reputation?

16:04.831 --> 16:08.234
Yeah. I am the best player
on the block.

16:08.268 --> 16:10.136
Cool.
Then how come you didn't win?

16:10.170 --> 16:12.172
Because you need
to be quiet, that's why.

16:12.205 --> 16:14.240
Don't tell me to be--!
[BOTH SHOUTING]

16:14.274 --> 16:16.409
Hey, hey, that's enough.
It's your problem.

16:16.443 --> 16:18.311
You borrowed it,
you pay it back.

16:18.345 --> 16:19.379
I am.

16:19.412 --> 16:22.182
I better not hear no more
about you betting money.

16:22.215 --> 16:25.218
Yes, ma'am.
All right.

16:25.251 --> 16:28.054
Mama, can we have
our candy--?

16:28.088 --> 16:29.589
No!

16:29.622 --> 16:31.524
I ate it.

16:31.558 --> 16:33.126
I don't need y'all getting

16:33.159 --> 16:35.261
any more cavities
than what y'all got.

16:35.295 --> 16:37.197
No cavities in this house.

16:37.230 --> 16:40.533
NARRATOR:
<i> But at this rate,</i>
<i>there'll be plenty of diabetes.</i>

16:40.567 --> 16:42.802
[GULPING LOUDLY]

16:52.412 --> 16:54.147
Needs more sugar.

16:56.383 --> 16:57.717
[YAWNS]

16:57.751 --> 16:59.586
You all right?

17:00.553 --> 17:01.821
Yeah, I'm just tired.

17:01.855 --> 17:03.423
I had this weird dream
last night

17:03.456 --> 17:05.859
and couldn't
fall back to sleep.

17:05.892 --> 17:08.094
Dream, huh?

17:08.128 --> 17:10.363
Yeah, it was bizarre.

17:10.397 --> 17:12.565
I was walking
down the street,

17:12.599 --> 17:14.567
waving hello
to everybody,

17:14.601 --> 17:16.603
but nobody was
waving back.

17:18.538 --> 17:21.174
It was as if
they couldn't see me.

17:21.207 --> 17:24.144
So you were invisible?
Yeah.

17:24.177 --> 17:26.746
NARRATOR:
<i>Mama had turtles,</i>
<i>Daddy had the lottery.</i>

17:26.780 --> 17:28.515
Oh, that's right...

17:28.548 --> 17:30.650
NARRATOR:
<i>It's a wonder</i>
<i>nobody sold the TV.</i>

17:30.684 --> 17:33.620
Come here. I need you to go to
the corner store after school

17:33.653 --> 17:36.723
and buy a lottery ticket for me.
Six-three-seven.

17:36.756 --> 17:38.525
Yeah, but you said
you weren't--

17:38.558 --> 17:40.326
I know what I said! Huh?

17:40.360 --> 17:42.262
I've just got a feeling
about this.

17:42.295 --> 17:45.532
NARRATOR:
<i>Translation: Just shut up</i>
<i>and do what I tell you.</i>

17:45.565 --> 17:47.801
Now, keep this between
me and you, all right?

17:47.834 --> 17:49.402
Six-three-seven,
all right?

17:49.436 --> 17:51.471
And keep the ticket on you.
Go! Go, go, go!

17:51.504 --> 17:54.174
NARRATOR:
<i>He hadn't been that excited</i>
<i>about a dream</i>

17:54.207 --> 17:55.742
<i>since Martin Luther King's.</i>

17:55.775 --> 17:57.877
[RADIO PLAYING]

18:01.247 --> 18:03.149
What do you need today?

18:03.183 --> 18:05.785
NARRATOR:
<i>My father played the lottery</i>
<i>a thousand times</i>

18:05.819 --> 18:07.420
<i>and lost a thousand times.</i>

18:07.454 --> 18:09.489
<i>I had only lost my rep once,</i>

18:09.522 --> 18:12.192
<i>and I wasn't about</i>
<i>to let that happen again.</i>

18:12.225 --> 18:14.694
Give me four quarters.

18:14.728 --> 18:16.296
Now you're talking.

18:16.329 --> 18:18.431
[***]

18:24.904 --> 18:27.273
Want to play me
for some more money?

18:27.307 --> 18:29.175
I don't have any money.

18:29.209 --> 18:31.611
I just want to prove
I can beat you.

18:39.619 --> 18:41.621
[GAME CHIMING]

18:41.654 --> 18:43.957
[MUTTERING]

18:43.990 --> 18:45.492
No...

18:45.525 --> 18:47.327
Aha! Ha-ha!

18:47.360 --> 18:50.730
Yes! Yes! Yes! Yes!

18:50.764 --> 18:53.266
What now, sucka? Ha!

18:53.299 --> 18:56.603
Good game, man.
You should've bet me, though.

18:56.636 --> 18:59.339
NARRATOR:
<i>If I had bet him,</i>
<i>I couldn't help but think</i>

18:59.372 --> 19:01.474
<i>that this would've happened...</i>

19:01.508 --> 19:03.810
Looks, good, huh?
JULIUS: I'm hungry.

19:03.843 --> 19:05.879
[***]

19:05.912 --> 19:08.281
Who are you?
I'm Jorge.

19:08.314 --> 19:10.517
I won your family from Chris
playing Asteroids.

19:10.550 --> 19:12.886
I told Chris
to stay out of that store.

19:12.919 --> 19:14.287
Can you cook mofongo?

19:14.320 --> 19:15.655
What?
What'd you call her?

19:15.689 --> 19:17.657
<i>Come tu comida.</i>

19:19.559 --> 19:21.628
I was raised around
Puerto Ricans.

19:21.661 --> 19:24.531
NARRATOR:
<i>There's something about</i>
<i>defending your reputation</i>

19:24.564 --> 19:26.900
<i>that makes you feel like you</i>
<i>accomplished something.</i>

19:26.933 --> 19:29.636
<i>And even though</i>
<i>I didn't get Greg's money back,</i>

19:29.669 --> 19:31.638
<i>I had my rep.</i>

19:31.671 --> 19:33.973
<i>Even though my father</i>
<i>never won the lottery,</i>

19:34.007 --> 19:35.508
<i>it always made him feel like</i>

19:35.542 --> 19:36.976
<i>there was one thing</i>
<i>in the world</i>

19:37.010 --> 19:38.645
<i>he had a shot at winning.</i>

19:38.678 --> 19:40.747
<i>And to him,</i>
<i>that dollar was worth it.</i>

19:40.780 --> 19:43.283
ANNOUNCER:
<i>And tonight's</i>
<i>winning numbers are...</i>

19:43.316 --> 19:45.985
<i>6...3...7.</i>

19:46.019 --> 19:49.456
I won! I won!

19:49.489 --> 19:50.457
I won!

19:50.490 --> 19:52.525
What happened?
My number hit!

19:52.559 --> 19:55.261
Chris, show your mama
the ticket.

19:55.295 --> 19:57.297
Show your mama the ticket, man!

19:58.798 --> 20:00.700
Show your mama
the ticket.

20:00.734 --> 20:05.572
Mama!
<i>* Everybody hates Chris </i>

20:07.073 --> 20:09.376
[***]

20:10.677 --> 20:14.014
<i>* Aw, make it funky now </i>
